cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as fuzzy logic programming is a subfield of AI and the paper discusses the automatic computation of appropriate values for parameters.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses integrating fuzzy logic into logic programming and the use of symbolic execution.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses a declarative programming paradigm and the specification of fuzzy logic programs.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses the tuning of fuzzy logic programs and the use of test cases.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as fuzzy logic is sometimes used in machine learning and the paper discusses the automatic computation of appropriate parameter values.
